<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-03-01T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-03-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="27" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/3–148: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-03-01T18:00:00-05:00">March 1, 1948—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>322. Supplementary surplus property agreement covering sale aircraft
                            engine overhaul plant equipment Hawaii signed Feb 28 and <pb facs="0036" n="26" xml:id="pg_26"/> payment received. (Sent Nanking as 322
                            repeated Shanghai as 370.)</p>
                        <p>Movement from Hickam Field depot to port will be made on request of
                            Chinese authorities.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>